Provision and deploy Rascal infrastructure resources.

Usage:
  rascal infra [flags]
  rascal infra [command]

Examples:
rascal infra up --provision --hcloud-token "$HCLOUD_TOKEN" --github-runtime-token "$RASCAL_GITHUB_TOKEN"
rascal infra provision-hetzner --token "$HCLOUD_TOKEN"
rascal infra deploy-existing --host "$SERVER_IP" --ssh-key ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

Available Commands:
  deploy-existing   Deploy rascald to an existing Linux host over SSH
  provision-hetzner Provision a Hetzner Cloud server
  up                Provision (optional) and deploy rascald

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for infra

Global Flags:
      --api-token string      orchestrator API token
      --config string         config file path (default "$HOME/.rascal/config.toml")
      --default-repo string   default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --env-file string       env file path (fallback: ./.rascal.env if present)
      --no-color              disable ANSI color/style output (also set by NO_COLOR)
      --output string         output format: table|json|toml (default "table")
  -q, --quiet                 reduce non-essential output
      --server-url string     orchestrator URL

Use "rascal infra [command] --help" for more information about a command.
